From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Spyros Seimenis <sespiros@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 18 Mar 2026 16:34:56 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] Sec: force SEV-ES termination for testing

Trigger an immediate SEV-ES guest termination (reason 0x0:0x0) at the
start of the SEC phase when SEV-ES is enabled. This reproduces the
kvm_amd 'SEV-ES guest requested termination: 0x0:0x0' kernel message
for testing kata runtime behavior when a CVM crashes during early boot.

This patch is for testing only and must not be used in production.
---
 .contrast-patch-dev-base    | 1 +
 .contrast-patch-dev-project | 1 +
 .contrast-patch-dev-repo    | 1 +
 OvmfPkg/Sec/SecMain.c       | 9 +++++++++
 4 files changed, 12 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 .contrast-patch-dev-base
 create mode 100644 .contrast-patch-dev-project
 create mode 100644 .contrast-patch-dev-repo

diff --git a/.contrast-patch-dev-base b/.contrast-patch-dev-base
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..ae565767f3abb5d907f1951c3e9e6b19072e899f
--- /dev/null
+++ b/.contrast-patch-dev-base
@@ -0,0 +1 @@
+46548b1adac82211d8d11da12dd914f41e7aa775
diff --git a/.contrast-patch-dev-project b/.contrast-patch-dev-project
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..1b24e1c2f474392a33b79910213ad2af5dfb4509
--- /dev/null
+++ b/.contrast-patch-dev-project
@@ -0,0 +1 @@
+ovmf-snp
diff --git a/.contrast-patch-dev-repo b/.contrast-patch-dev-repo
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..83455c5a29b513e5d87fb5c4034c024b8844bcb2
--- /dev/null
+++ b/.contrast-patch-dev-repo
@@ -0,0 +1 @@
+/Users/sespiros/git-pulls/edgelesssys/contrast
diff --git a/OvmfPkg/Sec/SecMain.c b/OvmfPkg/Sec/SecMain.c
index d13a9485094b491f465cef878b1faa85509adbe1..dca4dbeb041d4ee27d110b87362d01a9f58f2f8e 100644
--- a/OvmfPkg/Sec/SecMain.c
+++ b/OvmfPkg/Sec/SecMain.c
@@ -798,6 +798,15 @@ SecCoreStartupWithStack (
   UINT32                Index;
   volatile UINT8        *Table;
 
+  //
+  // Force an immediate SEV-ES guest termination for testing kata runtime
+  // behavior when a CVM crashes during early boot. This produces the
+  // kvm_amd "SEV-ES guest requested termination: 0x0:0x0" kernel message.
+  //
+  if (SevEsIsEnabled ()) {
+    SevEsProtocolFailure (0);
+  }
+
  #if defined (TDX_GUEST_SUPPORTED)
   if (CcProbe () == CcGuestTypeIntelTdx) {
     //
